headline: Treasury Yields Slide on Fresh Evidence US Economy Is Weakening
summary: (Bloomberg) -- Treasury yields declined to the lowest levels in nearly a month for most tenors after weaker-than-expected gauges of job creation and service-sector activity strengthened traders’ conviction that the Federal Reserve will resume cutting interest rates this year.Most Read from BloombergThe Global Struggle to Build Safer CarsAt London’s New Design Museum, Visitors Get Hands-On AccessICE Moves to DNA-Test Families Targeted for Deportation with New ContractLA City Council Passes Budget
